hotspot.title: Welcome!
hotspot.description: Nazareth Catholic Community is a place of welcome, connecting faith, family and education. Inspired by Jesus of Nazareth and our patrons we are people of justice each committed to building community, nourishing family life and making the world a better place.

hotspot.title: Reception
hotspot.description: Our Flinders Park campus welcomes Years 7 - 12 students from the College and their families as well as our wider community engagement programs.

hotspot.title: Sports Program
hotspot.description: Over 600 students compete for our College, with over 60 teams representing girls and boys summer and winter competitions. Opportunities also exist for participation in carnival, knockout competitions and other events. Our outstanding results speak for themselves and have significantly contributed to raising our college profile.

hotspot.title: Drop Down Curtain
hotspot.description: Drop down curtain to separate classes and physical education learning spaces allowing for different sports to be played at the same time

hotspot.title: Courts
hotspot.description: Indoor and outdoor basketball and netball courts, badminton and volleyball courts

hotspot.title: Academies
hotspot.description: Academies to develop skills in AFLW, netball, basketball and soccer with specialist coaches and access to intercol competitions

hotspot.title: EFM gym
hotspot.description: Access to EFM gym for training and conducting fitness testing.

hotspot.title: Oval
hotspot.description: Vast oval space to allow for all outdoor team sports to be played

hotspot.title: Cafe
hotspot.description: Creating a faith filled community of welcome and connection is a key part of our mission to nurture family life. Our community cafe’s on both sites are vibrant community hubs for families and community members to connect, meet or just relax with a great coffee and delicious snack or meal.

hotspot.title: Food and Beverages
hotspot.description: Provides quality, inexpensive food and beverages for Years 10, 11 & 12 supporting our local businesses.

hotspot.title: Year 12 Barista Training
hotspot.description: Barista training is available for Year 12 Students, providing the experience needed for future part time employment

hotspot.title: Inclusive Ed Creations
hotspot.description: Opportunities are provided for our Inclusive Education students, who regularly cook decadent biscuits to sell in the cafe.

hotspot.title: Caritas Downstairs
hotspot.description: The Caritas building allows us to cater for a wide range of learning styles in a contemporary, state of the art facility complete with seamless AV integration to support portable learning.

hotspot.title: Flexible Learning Spaces
hotspot.description: The flexible learning spaces create an adult learning environment to complement the transition of senior students into tertiary education, whilst allowing teaching staff the ability to create and present varied and diverse learning instructions to accommodate student need.

hotspot.title: Group Gatherings
hotspot.description: Flexibility allows for large group and year level or house gatherings.

hotspot.title: Kitchenettes
hotspot.description: Kitchenettes scattered throughout the building assist senior students in self-directed learning and breaks and communal conversation. The wide use of glass sliding doors, and floor to ceiling windows creates vision and a sense of space, and an abundance of natural light and welcoming environment allowing independent learning outside of the classroom.

hotspot.title: Performing Arts Space
hotspot.description: The expressive arts course engages students’ cognition, imagination, senses and emotions in conceptual and practical ways and involves them thinking kinaesthetically, critically and creatively. Students learn to understand, appreciate and critique the arts by making their own artworks. They also develop their ability to work collaboratively and creatively by devising, rehearsing and performing artworks.

hotspot.title: Versatile Large Space
hotspot.description: Versatile large space which acts as a classroom for Dance and Drama students as well as a theatre for Dance, Drama and Music performances.

hotspot.title: Studio Features
hotspot.description: Equipped with a sprung floor, tarquette, mirrors and black theatre curtains, which allow the space to be reconfigured for multiple purposes.

hotspot.title: Audio-visual Equipment
hotspot.description: Recently updated audio-visual equipment, including sound system, theatre lighting and industry standard lighting control systems.

hotspot.title: PAS
hotspot.description: The Performing Arts Space (PAS) is used to stage a number of performances throughout the year, including Dance, Drama and Music events.

hotspot.title: Special Events
hotspot.description: This flexible space also accommodates a range of guest speakers, presentations, workshops, assemblies and other special events

hotspot.url: media/Year 7 Expresssive Arts Hip Hop Final.mp4

hotspot.title: Veritas Centre
hotspot.description: Year 7 to 12 classes use the various areas in a flexible way for their research and reading needs. It is regularly used as a learning space for group work, study support with staff members, and a quiet space to study, read or browse our magazines and novels.

hotspot.title: Library
hotspot.description: The library is a communal space used well by students across all year levels where they may choose to either work independently, with a teacher or their peers.

hotspot.title: Student Focus
hotspot.description: A middle school focus on developing students’ note-making and paraphrasing skills, along with correct referencing and bibliography writing has been a focus as students move into their senior years of schooling. In the senior years a greater emphasis has been placed on accessing various online educational resource databases to promote greater depth of academic research.

hotspot.title: Tech
hotspot.description: Students can develop a broad range of skills and knowledge exploring a range of materials such as wood and metal, in addition to exposure to system concepts such as Computer Aided Design (CAD) and Advanced Manufacturing, Product Design, hydraulic devices and interface components including programmable control devices.

hotspot.title: Specialty Areas
hotspot.description: The area comprises of 3 main specialty areas. These are: Woodwork, Metalwork and advanced manufacturing, which includes 3D Printers, a Laser Cutter & Vinyl Cutter.

hotspot.title: Tech Pathways
hotspot.description: Design & Technology is an elective at Nazareth that is offered from Year 8 to Year 12. In year 8 & 9, students work through a 6 week rotation through the 3 areas, while in year 10, they can choose a more directed path.

hotspot.title: Autodesk Fusion 360
hotspot.description: Students use Autodesk Fusion 360 to design projects for manufacturing in a variety of materials.

hotspot.title: Pedal Prix
hotspot.description: Pedal Prix is also offered as a co-curricular sport, that the Design & Technology Faculty run.

hotspot.title: Arts Program
hotspot.description: Opportunities to experience and develop skills with a range of different materials and techniques, including drawing, painting, printmaking, sculpture, mixed media, graphic design and product design.

hotspot.title: Software Access
hotspot.description: Student access to Adobe Suite allows Arts students to work with industry-standard software and explore new media.

hotspot.title: Clay Area and Kiln
hotspot.description: Dedicated clay area and kiln for firing ceramic works.

hotspot.title: Workshops
hotspot.description: Workshops and curriculum extension with professional artists.

hotspot.title: Annual Art Exhibition
hotspot.description: Annual Art Exhibition and other opportunities for students to showcase their art work.

hotspot.title: Specialised Visual Arts Spaces
hotspot.description: Specialised visual arts learning spaces for senior and middle school classes with open plan design and natural light

hotspot.title: Three Laboratories
hotspot.description: Three laboratories tailoring to Biology, Chemistry/Physics and General Science

hotspot.title: Specialist Equipment
hotspot.description: Range of specialist equipment allowing for hands on investigations.

hotspot.title: Teacher Desk
hotspot.description: Science classrooms have teacher desks, with gas and water provisions for science demonstrations.

hotspot.title: Learning and success for all
hotspot.description: At Nazareth, we aspire to excellence in learning and success for all. We nurture a culture of achievement and personal excellence underpinned by strong leadership, high expectations, high quality teaching and learning, continuous improvement and strong home, school and community engagement.

hotspot.title: Partnership between home and school
hotspot.description: A strong partnership between home and school is the key to success so we are a community that is committed to strengthening families’ engagement in their children’s learning and wellbeing.

hotspot.title: Social justice principles
hotspot.description:
We are committed to the social justice principles of the Church, and, as stated in our Mission, are inspired by Jesus of Nazareth and our Patrons... each committed to building community, nourishing family life and making the world a better place.
Nazareth Outreach Projects (NOW) are an extension of our values and are supported by the entire community. We have an extensive array of projects we currently support. Our projects extend beyond Australia, with projects internationally, nationally as well as a local level.

hotspot.title: Five Habits of Excellence
hotspot.description: At Nazareth, we have adopted the Nazareth Five Habits of Excellence as a ‘roadmap’ to success.

hotspot.title: Student Leadership
hotspot.description: The Student leadership program at Nazareth provides opportunities for students to engage with the school community s well as the wider community. A wide range of leadership opportunities are available for students, with both elected positions and voluntary positions.
